Ex-KLA-Tencor, Juniper Lawyer to Pay $350,000 in SEC Settlement

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-10-19T16:51:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/ex-kla-tencor-juniper-lawyer-to-pay-350-000-in-sec-settlement.html
Lisa C. Berry, the former general
counsel of  KLA-Tencor Corp. (KLAC)  and  Juniper Networks Inc. (JNPR) , agreed to
settle Securities and Exchange Commission claims tied to option
backdating by paying a $350,000 civil penalty  Berry, who did not admit or deny the claims, also agreed to
pay disgorgement totaling $77,120, the SEC said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  